Costume-> Texture

Texture.... is the next selection found in the "Costume" menu.
 
The Texture editor is one of the more dramatic of MOVIEOLA tools. This
is because it can take a simple rectangular block and turn it into a
stone or brick wall with one button click.

The Texture editor like the Color editor should be invoked with an
object selected.

The Texture editor is divided into five basic sections:

In the upper left quarter of the editor is the translation, rotation
and scaling section. In the upper right-hand side is the texture
palette browser. In the bottom left quarter are the mapping controls,
and on the lower right side is the mapping preview window. This window
is used to quickly "preview" the texture mapping of the object before
it gets updated in the main scene. The "Image Information" window is
in the middle of the texture editor.


